    <title type="text">Digital Mishnah Update</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://dev.digitalmishnah.org/viewer/text/demo">Digital
      Mishnah</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><img
      alt="http://www.digitalmishnah.org/wp-content/themes/mishnah_2.0/images/mishnah-logo.png"
      class="decoded" height="47"
      src="http://www.digitalmishnah.org/wp-content/themes/mishnah_2.0/images/mishnah-logo.png"
      width="320" />&nbsp;</blockquote><blockquote
      class="tr_bq"><h2><span style="font-size: x-small;">About this
      demo</span></h2><span style="font-size: x-small;"> The <a
      class="highlighted" href="http://www.digitalmishnah.org/">Digital Mishnah Project</a>
      will provide users with a database of digitized manuscripts of the Mishnah from around the
      world, along with tools for collation, comparison, and analysis. This demo provides fully
      marked up transcriptions of twenty-two witnesses to a sample chapter, <cite>Bava
      Metsia</cite> ch 2, and illustrates basic functionalities. In a number of cases, the
      witnesses available for browse expand beyond the sample chapter to include all of Bava Qamma,
      Bava Metsi'a, and Bava Batra. </span><br /> <br />
      <table><tbody><tr> <td style="padding: 10px; vertical-align: top;">
      <form action="browse" class="buttons"> </form><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><br /></span></td> <td><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">The <a class="highlighted"
      href="http://dev.digitalmishnah.org/viewer/text/browse">browse</a> function presents
      metadata and a rendering of the transcription that which can be viewed with their metadata and
      approximately as laid out in the original text. </span></td>
      </tr><tr></tr><tr> <td style="padding: 10px; vertical-align:
      top;"> <form action="collate-hl" class="buttons"> </form><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></td> <td><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">The <a class="highlighted"
      href="http://dev.digitalmishnah.org/viewer/text/collate-hl">collate</a> function
      allows for the detailed comparison of witnesses. At its core it runs a set of texts through
      <a href="http://collatex.sourceforge.net/">CollateX</a>, which aligns matching
      words ("tokens"). The Digital Mishnah site remerges this output with the original textual data
      and represents the results both as an alignment table, and as a text with critical apparatus.
      The user can determine the passage, the witnesses, and the order. Because we anticipate that a
      number of users will prefer a parallel-column ("synoptic") presentation, the collate page shows
      an arrangement of the selected passage arranged in parallel columns by witness in the
      user-specified order.
      </span></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote><a
      href="http://mith.umd.edu/10126/">News on the New Version of Digital Mishnah
      Demo</a>]]></content>
